Relative frequency of each group of compounds present in the 10 most common 
   Citrus species. 
   Left, all the compounds described; 
   right outer circle, compounds up to date detected in only one species (one-species only); 
   right inner circle, compounds detected in all 10 species (common). Orange bars indicate separation between mono-, sesqui-, and other terpenoids, and non-terpenoid compounds. The qualitative data used is available in 
